{
  "texts": [
    "Meta-learning aims at enabling the AI model to learn how to learn, thus facilitating the high adaptation to new tasks.",
    "Specifically, unlike traditional learning approaches that train a dedicated AI model for the specific task, meta-learning aims at training a more general model on different tasks.",
    "which can quickly adapt to the new task with few training examples.",
    "However, all of these approaches inevitably result in high latency and computational resource requirements.",
    "Model complexityAlthough the AI model demonstrates a great potential in modeling various ISAC systems, it may need a complicated structure and an enormous number of learnable parameters to ensure the model accuracy."
  ]
}